originalText.text: I reserved through Spot Hero and was under the impression that I had paid all that was due and that was that. But when I returned, they wanted me to pay extra for the stay. Looking at the receipt, what I paid via Spot Hero was just the reservation and the actual parking service was separate. Which I could understand to a degree but it would have been nice if that was advertised. Other than that the attendant was generally friendly.

originalText.text: This is by far the worst garage I've ever used in New York City. No matter what time of the day it is they have one guy on, and that one guy often seems to have no idea how to work in a parking garage. You can call ahead by an hour for your car and it will still be parked three cars back and it will take them 20 minutes just to find your keys.  On top of that, some of the gentlemen are very nice, but some of them are extraordinarily rude. So rude sometimes you call for your car and you think you have the wrong number because the guy is yelling "I don't have any idea what you're talking about!" I mean these are pretty basic conversations. "I would like my car number x at y time of day." I know you're busy watching the TV blaring in the background but....  Finally, while it's not the most expensive garage in New York, it's not cheap. Maybe if I paid $200 a month I would put up with how terrible this place is but it's really shocking honestly. I have used lots of garages in New York but really never any place this bad. The employees here need a lot of training.

originalText.text: Don’t ruin your day and just go park somewhere else, unless you’re ok with being charged double the rate they give you. If you argue they will tell you we’re not bringing you your car until you pay. I’m feeling generous giving them a star.
